doc_summary_long: The extreme cold has pushed Ottawa well below the rest of the world's coldest capital cities. Mongolia's capital, Ulan Bator, is on average the coldest national capital in the world. But Ottawa's overnight temperature of -29 C on Wednesday fell below that for Ulaanbaatar, which experienced an overnight low of about -26 C.
